->To install git: sudo apt-get install git

->To configure git with GitHub: 
	git config --global user.name "user_name"
	git config --global user.email "email_id" 

->To initialize git: git init folder_name

->To add file/folder for commit: git add file_name/folder_name

->To remove file/folder for commit: git rm file_name/folder_name

->To check which files/folders are gonna be commit: git status

->To commit files/folders: git commit -m "some message"

->To undo "git add" or "git rm" before commit(i.e. you not want to commit all the files/folder you added): git reset file_name/folder_name

->To connect to remote repository on GitHub:
	git remote add origin https://github.com/user_name/repository_name.git

->To get repo from GitHub: git clone https://github.com/user_name/repository_name.git